# Defensive guard: Build.sh writes artifacts to its cwd. CMake stages a copy of
# this source tree into build/.cxx/.../mksh-build-<abi>/ before invoking
# Build.sh, so artifacts should never appear here. But if someone runs Build.sh
# manually in this directory (e.g. to debug), keep the diffs clean.
*.o
*.gen
*.cat1
mksh
mksh.exe
lksh
conftest.c
conftest
test.sh.bak
